  "synthesis": {
    "answer": "When the FalkorDB graph backend is unavailable, `gcode` degrades rather than hard-failing for optional graph reads: it returns hints, empty paginated responses, or `None` for graph-read failures [crates/gcode/src/commands/graph/reads.rs:14-20] [crates/gcode/src/commands/graph/reads.rs:50-73]. For required graph operations, it returns a `GraphReadError` mapped to service state like unavailable or unreachable [crates/gcode/src/graph/code_graph/connection.rs:14-40].",
